A member of the ANC. NELSPRUIT - It's all systems go for the ANC in Mpumalanga as it can now legally proceed with its elective conference after a failed court bid to stop it. The High Court in Pretoria has dismissed an urgent application to halt the ANC Mpumalanga provincial conference. READ: Application to halt ANC Mpumalanga conference dismissed It was brought by some unhappy ANC members, who allege there were irregularities. The ANC has welcomed the court ruling.  #ANCMPU @ANCMPUMALANGA delegates sing ahead of nominations for provincial leadership positions. The 13th ANC provincial conference is underway eMalahleni. #eNCA pic.twitter.com/6b6epAcKXE